		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName> <date>April 63d&#47;68</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">My dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Faithful to my&#44;<lb/> promise&#44; I solicited subscriptions<lb/> to your publications&#44; but have<lb/> only succeeded in procuring a<lb/> single name. There appears<lb/> &#40;as you so clearly explained to<lb/> me&#44; a want of manifest inte<lb/>rest in Jewish publications&#44; and<lb/> still less appreciation of Jewish<lb/> authors. When oh when will<lb/> you receive the reward which your<lb/> labours so e<add>&#63;</add> entitle<lb/> you to receive. I fear not until<lb/> a new spirit is infused in the<lb/> heart of <placeName>Israel</placeName>.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>Pardon me&#44; &#40;it may be <sic>presumtuous</sic>&#41;<lb/> if I solicit a reply to this.  My<lb/> inordinate thanks for the espousal<lb/> of <placeName>Judea&#39;s</placeName> cause makes me<lb/> bold enough to ask a correspondence<lb/> from <placeName>Judea&#39;s</placeName> guide.<lb/> Hoping that you are in the<lb/> enjoyment of the best of health<lb/> and an agreeable <date>Pesach</date>&#44;<lb/> I subscribe myself</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your very ob&#39;dt</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Simon Bachrach</persName></p>
				<p>Care of <persName>Rev. Dr. Lilienthal</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName><sic>Cincinatti</sic> O.</placeName></p>
				<p>Send 1 Vol. Meditations &#38;  Prayers to<lb/> <persName>Coblen&#39;s &#38;  Co.</persName><lb/> <placeName>180 Lexington St.</placeName></p>
				<p>Price &#36;2.50</p>
		</body>
